    <div class="hero__cover fade-up" style="--d:0.4s">
      <img
        class="book-cover"
        src="/images/book-cover.png"
        width="1027" height="1531"
        alt="Book cover: The Nervous System Field Manual — A Corpsman's Guide to the War Within, by Bobby L. Harris. Battlefield Essentials."
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ 2. AUTHORITY BAR ============ -->
<section class="authority">
  <div class="authority__track">
    <span class="authority__item"><span class="authority__icon">★</span> FMF Navy Corpsman</span>
    <span class="authority__sep">|</span>
    <span class="authority__item"><span class="authority__icon">⚕</span> OEF Veteran</span>
    <span class="authority__sep">|</span>
    <span class="authority__item"><span class="authority__icon">▮</span> Built from 18 Years of Field Testing</span>
    <span class="authority__sep">|</span>
    <span class="authority__item"><span class="authority__icon">✚</span> PTSD Recovery Survivor</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ 3. THE NORTH STAR ============ -->
<section class="section north-star reveal" id="north-star">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="label">THE NORTH STAR</p>
    <h2 class="display display--lg">
      Healing doesn't start in your head alone.<br />
      It starts by listening to the body.
    </h2>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Traditional talk therapy is often <strong>top-down</strong>. It helps you understand your
        emotions, patterns, and behaviors through insight and reflection. That can be valuable, but
        it doesn't always reach the parts of you that are still holding stress, tension, or trauma
        in the body.
      </p>
      <p>
        The field manual takes a <strong>bottom-up</strong> approach. Instead of starting with
        analysis, it starts with sensation. By noticing what your body is holding, you can help
        regulate your nervous system, release stored stress, and process emotional pain more deeply.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is the shift: from understanding pain only in your head to helping the body feel safe
        enough to let it move through.
      </p>
    </div>

    <blockquote class="pullquote">
      "Symptoms aren't good or bad. They're signals. The job is to resupply, not repair."
    </blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ 4. LETTER FROM BOBBY ============ -->
<section class="section letter-section reveal" id="letter">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <p class="label">LETTER FROM THE AUTHOR</p>
    <h2 class="display">What I Wish Someone Had Told Me.</h2>

    <article class="letter">
      <p>For eighteen years, I carried this weight that I could not identify.</p>
      <p>
        I went from doctor to doctor, and the answer was always the same: <em>anxiety</em>.
        Take this. Try that. It's all in your head. No one gave me an answer. No one could tell me
        why my body was still reacting in rooms that were already safe.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2023, I finally sat across from someone who did. A social worker saw the problem. He sat
        me down and had me look up the symptoms of PTSD, and for the first time, I had a real
        diagnosis. For the first time, this thing I'd been fighting had structure, context, and a name.
      </p>
      <p><strong>That was the turn.</strong></p>
      <p>
        I understood that my nervous system wasn't broken. It was trained. It had learned how to
        adapt to war, not how to come home and settle into civilian life. So I stopped trying to
        force repair and started learning how to read the signals my body was still sending. I built
        a kit, then tested it on my own body, day after day, for years.
      </p>
      <p>
        This manual is that kit. No theory you can't use tonight. No clinical distance. Just the
        tools that worked, written for the person still carrying the weight alone.
      </p>
      <p>You don't have to stay the person you were thirty days ago. Let's get to work.</p>

      <p class="letter__sign">— Bobby</p>
      <p class="letter__creds">
        FMF Navy Corpsman (2002–2009) &nbsp;|&nbsp; OEF Veteran &nbsp;|&nbsp; Founder, Battlefield Essentials
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ 5. WHAT'S INSIDE — SIX PILLARS ============ -->
<section class="section pillars-section reveal" id="whats-inside">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="label">THE OPERATIONAL SYSTEM</p>
    <h2 class="display">Six Pillars. Thirty Days. One Working Kit.</h2>

    <div class="pillars">
      <% const pillars = [
        ['1','ORIENT','The 90-Second Reset. Prove to yourself on Day 1 that your nervous system can be reached.'],
        ['2','ASSESS','The Symptom-to-Tool Triage Chart. Match the right tool to the right symptom in real time.'],
        ['3','EQUIP','The Seven-Tool Kit. Your full arsenal. Know which three are yours.'],
        ['4','EXECUTE','The 45-Minute Operator System. Stop running a 12-hour shift. Run sixteen 45-minute operations.'],
        ['5','SUSTAIN','The Two-Sentence Containment Practice. Rebuild the wire between mission and home.'],
        ['6','ADAPT','The Personal Field Update. Your monthly after-action review. The kit gets sharper every cycle.']
      ]; %>
      <% pillars.forEach(function(p){ %>
        <article class="pillar reveal">
          <div class="pillar__badge"><%= p[0] %></div>
          <h3 class="pillar__name">PILLAR <%= p[0] %> — <%= p[1] %></h3>
          <p class="pillar__desc"><%= p[2] %></p>
        </article>
      <% }); %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ 6. THE SEVEN TOOLS ============ -->
<section class="section tools-section reveal" id="tools">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="label">THE TOOLKIT</p>
    <h2 class="display">Seven Tools. Pick Three. Carry Three. Master Three.</h2>

    <ol class="tools">
      <% const tools = [
        ['90-Second Visual Orienting Reset','Baseline tension, pre-shift dread'],
        ['Long Exhale Stack (4-in / 8-out)','0300 wake-up, sleep, anxiety spike'],
        ['Box Breathing (4-4-4-4)','Pre-shift, focus reset, pre-confrontation'],
        ['5-4-3-2-1 Sensory Grounding','Irritability, dissociation, spiral'],
        ['Physical Contact Drill','Dissociation, numbness, floating'],
        ['Bilateral Movement Drill','Brain fog, stuck, transitions'],
        ['One-Sentence Containment Write','End of shift, before bed']
      ]; %>
      <% tools.forEach(function(t, i){ %>
        <li class="tool reveal">
          <span class="tool__num"><%= i + 1 %></span>
          <div class="tool__body">
            <h3 class="tool__name"><%= t[0] %></h3>
            <p class="tool__use"><%= t[1] %></p>
          </div>
        </li>
      <% }); %>
    </ol>

    <blockquote class="pullquote pullquote--center">
      "When in doubt, run Tool 1. Always free. Always works."
    </blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ 7. WHO THIS IS FOR ============ -->
<section class="section unit-section reveal" id="who">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="label">YOUR UNIT</p>
    <h2 class="display">Built for Anyone Carrying It Alone.</h2>

    <div class="unit-grid">
      <% const unit = [
        ['🪖','Veterans'],
        ['⚓','Active-Duty Military'],
        ['🚒','First Responders'],
        ['🏋️','Tactical Athletes'],
        ['💼','Shift Workers'],
        ['🧠','Diagnosed or Suspected PTSD']
      ]; %>
      <% unit.forEach(function(u){ %>
        <div class="unit reveal">
          <span class="unit__icon"><%= u[0] %></span>
          <span class="unit__label"><%= u[1] %></span>
        </div>
      <% }); %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ 8. WHAT YOU WILL HAVE ============ -->
<section class="section deliverables-section reveal" id="deliverables">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <p class="label">THE DELIVERABLES</p>
    <h2 class="display">By Day 30, You Will Have:</h2>

    <ul class="checklist">
      <% const deliverables = [
        'A personalized triage chart matched to your five most common symptoms',
        'Three tools you have run on your own body more than fifteen times each',
        'A shift map for the operation you actually live',
        'A two-sentence log you can read back to yourself',
        'A written debrief of what changed',
        'Proof, in your own handwriting, that you are not the same man you were 30 days ago'
      ]; %>
      <% deliverables.forEach(function(d){ %>
        <li class="check reveal"><span class="check__mark">✓</span><span><%= d %></span></li>
      <% }); %>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

